<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Anti-ESG</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">My basic view of bubbles is that if you can id=
entify a bubble, and you have some free time, the right move is to sell int=
o the bubble. Not sell=C2=A0<em>short</em>, mind you, which is risky; you d=
on=E2=80=99t know when the bubble will=C2=A0pop. Sell <em>long</em>. Get in=
to the business that is bubbly, because that=E2=80=99s where the money is. =
There is demand; become the supply. My <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/29339418.286265/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcG=
luaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTktMTAtMjMvaG93LWRvLXlvdS1saWtlLXdlLW5vdz9jbXBpZD1CQ=
kQxMDExMjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRl=
ciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjEwMTEmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cB042411a5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;"> model of Adam Neumann</a> is that he correctly ide=
ntified a huge bubble in venture funding for fast-growing not-quite-tech co=
mpanies, positioned himself in front of a=C2=A0firehose of SoftBank money, =
and became dynastically wealthy as that bubble popped. He was the Big Short=
 of the recent tech bubble, but without the timing risk of actually selling=
 short.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or in=C2=A02017 every random micro-cap public =
company <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29339418.2=
86265/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTctMTItM=
jEvYmxvY2tjaGFpbnMtZ28td2VsbC13aXRoLWNvY2t0YWlscz9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMDExMjJfTU9O=
RVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0=
yMjEwMTEmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9a4b907d"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;"> pivoted to the blockchain</a>. Correctly!<a class=3D"footnote-ind=
ex" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; displ=
ay: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Similarly with the=C2=A0rise of environmental,=
 social and governance investing over the last few years. As an=C2=A0<em>in=
vestor</em>, you might have views like =E2=80=9CESG is a fad and I will sho=
rt stocks that are popular with ESG funds, betting that their valuations wi=
ll collapse,=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9CESG is a rising trend and I will get long=
 stocks that have good ESG scores, betting that there will be continued dem=
and for them,=E2=80=9D<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" styl=
e=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width:=
 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; b=
ackground-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>=C2=A0and these are hard calls to make and require timing. But if you w=
ere just, like, looking around for something to do, surely starting an inve=
stment fund or consultancy or ratings firm or whatever and saying =E2=80=9C=
we will be very very ESG indeed=E2=80=9D was a good=C2=A0<em>marketing </em=
>strategy. Slapping an =E2=80=9CESG=E2=80=9D label on things allowed you to=
 charge high fees and raise a lot of money, and people did.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But in recent months <a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29339418.286265/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJ=
nLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDktMDEvdGhlLXRydW1wLXNwYWMtbmVlZHMtbW=
9yZS10aW1lP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEwMTEyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX=
3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMTAxMSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVm=
Zg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB34281718" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">there has been a=C2=A0vogue f=
or=C2=A0<em>anti-</em>ESG</a>, and whatever you think of its merits it is j=
ust an obviously lucrative market to sell into.=C2=A0Right now, if you go a=
round saying =E2=80=9CI am going to do a financial business, but I will mak=
e a point of not considering environmental, social or governance factors,=
=E2=80=9D or even =E2=80=9CI <em>will </em>consider ESG=C2=A0factors, but o=
nly to do the <em>opposite</em><em>=C2=A0</em>of what those =E2=80=98woke=
=E2=80=99 ESG funds do,=E2=80=9D people will fling money at you. You can wa=
lk into Peter Thiel=E2=80=99s office wearing a clown suit and say =E2=80=9C=
high-frequency trading, but anti-woke,=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Cpayday lending,=
 but anti-woke,=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Cvariable annuities, but anti-woke,=E2=
=80=9D or =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click=
/29339418.286265/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLz=
IwMjAtMDctMTcvZnJlZS10cmFkZXMtY2FuLXJlYWxseS1jb3N0LXlvdT9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMDExM=
jJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1f=
dGVybT0yMjEwMTEmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB30=
48b125" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;">capped/uncapped variance swaps</a>, but anti-woke,=E2=80=9D=
 or whatever, and he will write you a big check. =E2=80=9C_____ but not ESG=
=E2=80=9D is a business model that can raise money right now, so why aren=
=E2=80=99t you doing it?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One subtle advantage of this business model is=
 that a way to signal that you are authentically anti-ESG is by having <em>=
bad governance</em>, since =E2=80=9Cgovernance=E2=80=9D is right there in t=
he name of the thing you (and your investors)=C2=A0are against. This can wo=
rk to your advantage: Bad governance tends to be bad for investors but good=
 for entrepreneurs. (Ask <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com=
/click/29339418.286265/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGlj=
bGVzLzIwMTktMDgtMTkvd2UtbG9va3Mtb3V0LWZvci1vdXItc2VsdmVzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEwMTE=
yMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV=
90ZXJtPTIyMTAxMSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf=
350b1d1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;">  Adam Neumann</a>!)=C2=A0You raise a bunch of money and t=
hen spend it on yachts for yourself, and your investors=C2=A0say things lik=
e =E2=80=9Cwell the governance of this company is pretty bad isn=E2=80=99t =
it,=E2=80=9D and you=C2=A0say =E2=80=9Cexactly!=E2=80=9D Bad governance is =
what they signed up for!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/29339418.286265/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy=
9nbG9yaWZpLWhvdy1uZXctYW50aS13b2tlLWJhbmstc3R1bWJsZWQtMTE2NjUxNzQ3MDQ/607f0=
7ceef4b8524a319a23cB34e2776b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope=
" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importa=
nt; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-s=
tyle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Wall Street Journal article</a> about=
 an =E2=80=9Canti-woke bank=E2=80=9D that just reads all the way through li=
ke a parody, which is how you know it=E2=80=99s a good idea:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The startup, called GloriFi, initially aimed t=
o launch with bank accounts, credit cards, mortgages and insurance, while t=
outing what it called pro-America values such as capitalism, family, law en=
forcement and the freedom to =E2=80=9Ccelebrate your love of God and countr=
y.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Within months, the investors=E2=80=99 money wa=
s nearly gone, and GloriFi was on the verge of bankruptcy. It missed launch=
 dates, blaming faulty technology and failures by vendors, and laid off doz=
ens of employees. It stumbled with products; for instance, a plan to make a=
 credit card out of the same material used for shell casings failed when th=
e company realized the material could interfere with security chips and pot=
entially be too thick for payment terminals, according to people familiar w=
ith the matter.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sure! Look, you can=E2=80=99t actually make cr=
edit cards out of bullets, but in 2022 you can <em>raise infinity dollars=
=C2=A0</em>by walking into the right room and=C2=A0saying the words =E2=80=
=9Cmake credit cards out of bullets.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0<em>That=C2=A0</em>is th=
e financial innovation here.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">GloriFi=E2=80=99s founder, Toby Neugebauer,=C2=
=A0is =E2=80=9Cthe son of a former Texas congressman=E2=80=9D and an oil-an=
d-gas investor. And there=E2=80=99s this:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Of the criticism of his alleged dr=
inking, he said, =E2=80=9CThe attacks on what I do in my home after 5 p.m. =
are beneath=E2=80=9D The Wall Street Journal. =E2=80=A6</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Which I would say is generally a fair point, e=
xcept that his home was also the headquarters of the company, and what=C2=
=A0he=C2=A0allegedly does in his home after 5 p.m. is drink and berate the =
employees who work there:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. Neugebauer=E2=80=99s 16,000-square-foot Da=
llas home, modeled after the White House, became the company=E2=80=99s init=
ial headquarters.=C2=A0=E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But staffers began complaining about what they=
 said were Mr. Neugebauer=E2=80=99s volatile behavior and drinking habits, =
according to people familiar with the matter and a memo from Britt Amos, Gl=
oriFi=E2=80=99s former head of human resources, reviewed by the Journal. Ms=
. Amos left in the spring after clashing with Mr. Neugebauer, and she recou=
nted issues she saw as problems in the memo.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CSeveral people working at the mansion=
 told me to make sure I leave around six,=E2=80=9D Ms. Amos wrote in the me=
mo. =E2=80=9CWhen I inquired why, they stated that after 5 p.m. Toby starts=
 drinking and things at the house deteriorate quickly.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Presumably this scores very low on the=C2=A0go=
vernance part of ESG checklists, which is what they=E2=80=99re going for. A=
nother anti-ESG entrepreneur, Vivek Ramaswamy, also makes an appearance:</p=
>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Around this time, one of GloriFi=E2=80=99s inv=
estors, Vivek Ramaswamy, was working to launch his own financial-services f=
irm. Strive Asset Management would offer investors an alternative to firms =
such as BlackRock Inc., which has pushed companies to improve diversity and=
 cut their climate emissions, among other changes. Strive, instead, would p=
ush companies to focus on making money, not taking stands on social or poli=
tical issues.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. Neugebauer said he was furious and was con=
vinced that Mr. Ramaswamy, who wrote the book =E2=80=9CWoke, Inc.,=E2=80=9D=
 had stolen his idea. Mr. Neugebauer said he had even invested in Strive, t=
hinking it was a conservative beer startup.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Asset management! Beer! It doesn=E2=80=99t mat=
ter! The product is not the point.</p>
