target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  say</a> that the fate of all crypto e=
xchanges was to be hacked, but in fairness that has stopped being true. Big=
 modern crypto exchanges tend to be serious professional companies that car=
e a lot about information security, and when one is=C2=A0hacked and <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29339418.286265/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuY25iYy5jb20vMjAyMi8xMC8wNy9tb3JlLXRoYW4tMTAwLW1pbGxpb24td29ydGgtb2Yt=
YmluYW5jZXMtYm5iLXRva2VuLXN0b2xlbi1pbi1hbm90aGVyLW1ham9yLWNyeXB0by1oYWNrLmh=
0bWw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7694f4a2" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> loses=C2=A0$570 million of=
 crypto</a>, that is=C2=A0<em>news</em>, as opposed to just, you know, Thur=
sday. It still happens though. There is some combination of factors that ma=
kes exchanges=E2=80=99 pots of customer crypto=C2=A0just irresistible to ha=
ckers, something like:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Cryptocurrencies are more or less bear=
er instruments, so if you steal a bunch of Bitcoin you can use them more ea=
sily than if you steal a bunch of Treasury bonds or whatever.</li>=09<li st=
yle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Computer hackers tend to be intellectually and =
aesthetically interested in crypto, so they focus their hacking energies on=
 crypto exchanges rather than banks.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px=
;">Crypto is pretty thinly regulated, so you are somewhat less likely to at=
tract law-enforcement attention for hacking a crypto exchange than for hack=
ing a bank.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Crypto is all pretty n=
ew, so there is less in the way of best practices around information securi=
ty.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Crypto exchanges mostly aren=
=E2=80=99t just one guy with a laptop anymore, but they are still <em>more<=
/em> likely to be <em>closer</em> to =E2=80=9Cone guy with a laptop=E2=80=
=9D than the average=C2=A0bank<em>=C2=A0</em>is.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I say =E2=80=9Ccrypto exchanges=E2=80=9D becau=
se, historically, crypto exchanges have been leaders=C2=A0in the business o=
f keeping custody of crypto assets. But now crypto custody is increasingly =
the business of=C2=A0traditional financial institutions. And I guess the qu=
estion is: Wouldn=E2=80=99t it be very, very funny if Bank of New York Mell=
on Corp. gets hacked and loses <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/29339418.286265/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9hbWVyaW=
Nhcy1vbGRlc3QtYmFuay1ibnktbWVsbG9uLXdpbGwtaG9sZC10aGF0LWNyeXB0by1ub3ctMTE2N=
jU0NjAzNTQ_bW9kPWhwX2xlYWRfcG9zNA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9c515d44" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
"> its customers=E2=80=99 Bitcoin</a>?</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The nation=E2=80=99s oldest bank said it would=
 begin receiving clients=E2=80=99 cryptocurrencies on Tuesday, becoming the=
 first large U.S. bank to safeguard digital assets alongside traditional in=
vestments on the same platform. =C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">BNY Mellon won the approval of New York=E2=80=
=99s financial regulator earlier this fall to begin receiving select custom=
ers=E2=80=99 bitcoin and ether starting this week. The bank will store the =
keys required to access and transfer those assets, and provide the same boo=
kkeeping services on those digital currencies that it offers to fund manage=
rs for their portfolios of stocks, bonds, commodities and other assets. ...=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Money managers have long relied on BNY Mellon =
and other custody banks for an array of vital, if humdrum, back-office func=
tions such as tracking changes to the value of their assets. Founded by Ale=
xander Hamilton more than two centuries ago, BNY Mellon is the world=E2=80=
=99s biggest custody bank.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Until now, fund managers would have had to cus=
tody their digital currencies with a crypto specialist. BNY Mellon said it =
is the first of the eight systemically important U.S. banks to store digita=
l currencies and allow customers to use one custody platform for both its t=
raditional and crypto holdings.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWe are excited to help drive the fina=
ncial industry forward,=E2=80=9D Robin Vince, BNY Mellon=E2=80=99s presiden=
t and chief executive, said in a statement.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It probably won=E2=80=99t happen, right? The p=
oint of doing crypto custody with BNY Mellon, as opposed to =E2=80=9Ca cryp=
to specialist,=E2=80=9D is that you are expecting the security, regulation,=
 and not-being-hacked-too-much of traditional finance. Still you might worr=
y: BNY Mellon=E2=80=99s pot of crypto=C2=A0will be as attractive to hackers=
 as any crypto exchange=E2=80=99s pot of crypto, and it might have=C2=A0<em=
>less=C2=A0</em>experience and expertise in securing crypto than =E2=80=9Ca=
 crypto specialist=E2=80=9D would. The question is whether being hacked con=
stantly is a feature of crypto=C2=A0<em>exchanges</em>, or just a feature o=
f=C2=A0<em>crypto</em>.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elsewhere in <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/29339418.286265/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlZ3VhcmRpYW4uY29=
tL3RlY2hub2xvZ3kvMjAyMi9vY3QvMTEvY3J5cHRvLWNvbS1hY2NpZGVudGFsLXRyYW5zZmVyLT=
EwLTUtbWlsbGlvbi10cmlhbC1hdXN0cmFsaWEtY291cGxlLWNyeXB0b2N1cnJlbmN5/607f07ce=
ef4b8524a319a23cB70b34309" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" t=
arget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: solid; background-color: #ccc;">crypto custody</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A Victorian woman accused of theft over a $10.=
5m mistaken cryptocurrency refund has been released on bail as she awaits t=
rial, despite claims she allegedly tried to flee the country.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Thevamanogari Manivel and her partner, Jatinde=
r Singh, appeared by video link from prison in Melbourne magistrates court =
on Tuesday when they were committed to stand trial on theft and other charg=
es.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In May 2021, Crypto.com intended to refund Man=
ivel $100 but she was erroneously transferred $10.47m. The company did not =
notice the mistake until an audit was conducted in December.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A worker in Bulgaria, who processed the refund=
, had entered the wrong numbers into an Excel spreadsheet, Michi Chan Fores=
, a Crypto.com compliance officer, told the court.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It would be funny if =E2=80=9Cthe blockchain=
=E2=80=9D was just a euphemism for =E2=80=9Can Excel spreadsheet.=E2=80=9D<=
/p>
