<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/29339418.286265/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vM=
jAyMi8xMC8wNi90ZWNobm9sb2d5L2Vsb24tbXVzay10d2l0dGVyLXRyaWFsLmh0bWwjOn46dGV4=
dD1JbiUyMHJlY2VudCUyMHdlZWtzJTJDJTIwTXIuJTIwTXVzayxhJTIwbGF3eWVyJTIwcmVwcmV=
zZW50aW5nJTIwTXIuJTIwTXVzay4/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb8c255c1" itemprop=3D=
"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">ano=
ther way</a>=C2=A0that Elon Musk=E2=80=99s deal to buy Twitter Inc. could h=
ave gone:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In recent weeks, Mr. Musk proposed buying Twit=
ter at a discount of as much as 30 percent. Discussions later narrowed to a=
round 10 percent, people familiar with those conversations said.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Twitter appeared willing to negotiate on the p=
rice, said Alex Spiro, a lawyer representing Mr. Musk.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CTwitter offered Mr. Musk billions off=
 the transaction price. Mr. Musk refused because Twitter attempted to put c=
ertain self-serving conditions on the deal,=E2=80=9D Mr. Spiro said, withou=
t adding more details. A Twitter spokesman declined to respond to a request=
 for comment on the claim.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On Monday, after those conversations had fizzl=
ed, Mr. Musk informed the company that he was ready to proceed with the ori=
ginal price he offered in April.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What were those =E2=80=9Cself-serving conditio=
ns=E2=80=9D? It seems like one of them might have been something to the eff=
ect of =E2=80=9Cbut you actually have to pay,=E2=80=9D like:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Twitter:</strong> Okay we=E2=80=99ll d=
o $50 per share, but you have to promise not to come to us tomorrow with so=
me new insane excuse for why you won=E2=80=99t close.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Musk:</strong> No deal!</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This sort of condition would be=C2=A0pretty st=
andard. We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2933941=
8.286265/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMD=
YtMTMvbWVyZ2VyLWJ1eWVyLXMtcmVtb3JzZS1zb21ldGltZXMtd29ya3M_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTAxM=
TIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRt=
X3Rlcm09MjIxMDExJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf=
a8c96c4" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;">  have talked about</a> Thoma Bravo=E2=80=99s deal for Ana=
plan Inc., for instance. Thoma Bravo shamelessly retraded on the agreed pri=
ce, and Anaplan gave it a 3.4% price cut, but in exchange Thoma Bravo essen=
tially waived all of its=C2=A0conditions, requirements, etc., and agreed to=
 close no matter what.=C2=A0I suggested this as a possible model for Twitte=
r and Musk repricing their deal, but apparently it didn=E2=80=99t work.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another =E2=80=9Cself-serving condition=E2=80=
=9D might have been something to the effect of =E2=80=9Cokay, we=E2=80=99ll=
 give you a price cut, but when shareholders sue us personally, you=E2=80=
=99ll defend us and pay any judgment.=E2=80=9D It=C2=A0<em>would=C2=A0</em>=
have been kind of self-serving for Twitter=E2=80=99s directors to give Musk=
 a price cut (which comes out of the pockets of their shareholders) in exch=
ange for reducing their=C2=A0risk of=C2=A0<em>personal=C2=A0</em>liability.=
 Also it might not have worked out to be a price cut, really:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Twitter=E2=80=99s directors cut the p=
rice from $54.20 to $50; the deal closes.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom=
: 5px;">Shareholders sue, saying =E2=80=9Cyou had a good deal at $54.20, it=
 was ironclad, and you disloyally gave some of that back to Musk=C2=A0for y=
our own personal convenience.=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5=
px;">This is correct, and they win a judgment of $4.20 per share, plus inte=
rest.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Musk pays it.</li>=09<li sty=
le=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Might as well have just paid $54.20 in the first=
 place, no?</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If that was the sticking point, you can see wh=
y Musk would say no. A <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/c=
lick/29339418.286265/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLz=
IwMjItMTAtMDYvbXVzay10d2l0dGVyLXJlc29sdXRpb24tc2FpZC10by1zdGljay1vbi1kZWJ0L=
